    {
      "id": "74c03dba_3cf0aac5",
      "file_path": "cps-application/src/test/java/org/onap/cps/architecture/LayeredArchitectureTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 13,
      "line": 46,
      "message": "Is CPS API really used by NCMP rest controller? I don't see any references to _org.onap.cps.api_ inside _cps-ncmp-rest_ module. I think Rest packages should depend on corresponding API package:\n- CPS Rest -> CPS API\n- NCMP Rest -> NCMP API",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
      "updated": "2024-10-08 11:45:38.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "f2c7e0c8_295d7477",
      "file_path": "cps-application/src/test/java/org/onap/cps/architecture/LayeredArchitectureTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 13,
      "line": 58,
      "message": "Currently, ncmp.api does depend on ncmp.impl, but it really shouldn't. This should be considered a violation IMO",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
      "updated": "2024-10-08 11:45:38.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "a5b34c68_572b06a3",
      "file_path": "cps-application/src/test/java/org/onap/cps/architecture/LayeredArchitectureTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 13,
      "line": 59,
      "message": "Is this a current dependency? NCMP *API* should not depend CPS API, rather NCMP impl may depend on CPS. Either way, I don't see any package imports to _org.onap.cps.api_ inside _org.onap.cps.ncmp.api_.\n\n@Toine should we be adding rules for dependencies that don't currently exist?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
